in the nGOM, corresponding to a maximum potential annual output of
2,332,490 eggs for an average sized (188.6 g) female. These reproductive
characteristics are similar to invasive lionfish in tropical waters,
although nGOM reproductive output appears higher. Our results represent
the most comprehensive reproductive data on lionfish in their invaded
range, and provide a baseline for management in the nGOM.},
