e findings indicate that sex differentiation in southern flounder is distinguishable in most fish by 100-120 mm TL and that sex determination is sensitive to temperature. This information is critical to the development of strategies to maximize the number of faster-growing females for commercial flounder culture. {\textcopyright} 2003 Elsevier Science B.V. All rights reserved.},
